race.comment: Competitive. JOHNNIE PINCH (11) is a leader who tumbles in weight seeking the hat-trick off an easy win in a 60 here over this distance. Has a top senior hoop aboard today replacing the 3kg apprentice. He will push forward and will take catching. DISTRUSTFUL AWARD (1) has needed the two runs this preparation but is proven third-up. He's raced well in Victoria in stronger than this and can feature with average luck in the run. KALIUWAA FALLS (2) rates up to this but hasn't won for 15 starts and 506 days. He's suited regardless and he gets his chance going on the strength of his latest run. SPRING BEAN (6) is capable and will be a lot more competitive back on turf. Maps well and 2x winning rider Newitt is reunited. GOLDEN PROPHET (10) wasn't given a hope in the Summer Cup at Hobart and raced accordingly. Placed in the Brighton Cup prior and is much better suited today. Needs a good ride but he can get into the finish.
